n religious traditions have abandoned their own intellectual cultures so drastically that no one has any sense of it other than the fringe.', 1383, 0), (455725, 'I''ve got no problem with anybody''s religion. But if you go claiming the Earth is only 10,000 years old, that''s just wrong.', 13455, 0), (455726, 'When I talk about God, I''m not necessarily talking about religion. To me, God is the energy and light that each of us carries.', 67930, 0), (455727, 'A true Christian, who is born anew of the Spirit of Christ, is in the simplicity of Christ, and hath no strife or contention with any man about religion.', 5825, 0), (455728, 'We need great prophetic leaders in religion and in spirituality... what we are getting is lacking in vision... not able to engage with the diversity of the culture.', 400, 0), (455729, 'That I am not a member of any Christian church is true; but I have never denied the truth of the Scriptures, and I have never spoken with intentional disrespect of religion in general, or of any denomination of Christians in particular.', 1012, 0), (455730, 'Tolerance says I am just going to stomach your right to be different. That if you disappear from the face of the earth, I am no better or worse off. But love - love knows that every American has worth and value, no matter what their background, race, religion, or sexual orientation.', 10615, 0), (455731, 'It''s not surprising, then, they get bitter, they cling to guns or religion or antipathy to people who aren''t like them or anti-immigrant sentiment or anti-trade sentiment as a way to explain their frustrations.', 1693, 0), (455732, 'Being religious means asking passionately the question of the meaning of our existence and being willing to receive answers, even if the answers hurt.', 2750, 0), (455733, 'Religion and slavery are incompatible.', 5224, 0), (455734, 'You have this mounting aggressive ignorance with the rabbit''s foot of their particular religion. You don''t really have any kind of spiritual law, just a kind of a rabid mental illness. The songs are a little slice of life.', 16696, 0), (455735, 'God has to speak to each person in their own language, in their own idioms. Take Spanish, Chinese. You can express the same thought, but to different people you have to use a different language. It''s the same in religion.', 7993, 0), (455736, 'True religion is real living; living with all one''s soul, with all one''s goodness and righteousness.', 104, 0), (455737, 'I don''t believe in God but I''m very interested in her.', 1004, 0), (455738, 'Religion is more like response to a friend than it is like obedience to an expert.', 72767, 0), (455739, 'I never saw, heard, nor read, that the clergy were beloved in any nation where Christianity was the religion of the country. Nothing can render them popular, but some degree of persecution.', 995, 0), (455740, 'There was a time when someone would get on a plane and request to move their seat just because the person sitting next to them was of a different ethnicity or religion or nationality. But I don''t think my generation wants that. That''s how it used to be.', 66683, 0), (455741, 'Surely the day will come when color means nothing more than the skin tone, when religion is seen uniquely as a way to speak one''s soul, when birth places have the weight of a throw of the dice and all men are born free, when understanding breeds love and brotherhood.', 52279, 0), (455742, 'The Twist was a guided missile launched from the ghetto into the heart of suburbia. The Twist succeeded, as politics, religion and law could never do, in writing in the heart and soul what the Supreme Court could only write on the books.', 63025, 0), (455743, 'Religion without humanity is very poor human stuff.', 2013, 0), (455744, 'So potent was religion in persuading to evil deeds.', 63809, 0), (455745, 'Religion is more than life. Remember that his own religion is the truest to every man even if it stands low in the scales of philosophical comparison.', 32, 0), (455746, 'Educate men without religion and you make of them but clever devils.', 14558, 0), (455747, 'For as long as I care to remember, religion, like the striptease, has always been a display of the power of suggestion. Like the Virgin Birth, it has all too often supported an immaculate deception.', 72768, 0), (455748, 'The artist himself may not think he is religious, but if he is sincere his sincerity in itself is religion.', 37762, 0), (455749, 'Moral values, and a culture and a religion, maintaining these values are far better than laws and regulations.', 62960, 0), (455750, 'Even though you can''t expect to defeat the absurdity of the world, you must make the attempt. That''s morality, that''s religion, that''s art, that''s life.', 17659, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (455751, 'The Constitution provides for freedom of religion, not freedom from religion.', 72769, 0), (455752, 'There is a great difference between Christianity and religion at the south. If a man goes to the communion table, and pays money into the treasury of the church, no matter if it be the price of blood, he is called religious.', 70830, 0), (455753, 'Personally, I don''t choose any particular religion or symbol or group of words or teachings to define me. That''s between me and the most high. You know, my higher self. The Creator.', 964, 0), (455754, 'The basic assumption of the secular society is that modernity overcomes religion.', 66823, 0), (455755, 'A universe with a God would look quite different from a universe without one. A physics, a biology where there is a God is bound to look different. So the most basic claims of religion are scientific. Religion is a scientific theory.', 1716, 0), (455756, 'Even if it were proven that God didn''t exist, Religion would still be Saintly and Divine.', 1165, 0), (455757, 'Religion is love in no case is it logic.', 72770, 0), (455758, 'To criticize a person for their race is manifestly irrational and ridiculous, but to criticize their religion, that is a right. That is a freedom.', 16706, 0), (455759, 'Communism was meant to be an alternative religion.', 72771, 0), (455760, 'I think people''s perception of a rich girl is literal, but metaphorically I embrace it as being rich in love, spirit, joy and religion. So it''s not about money.', 52738, 0), (455761, 'I don''t think the 9/11 attacks taught us anything we didn''t already know about religion. It has long been obvious - even to the deeply religious - that religious fanaticism is an extremely dangerous deranger of otherwise sane and goodhearted people.', 38978, 0), (455762, 'Keeping religion immune from criticism is both unwarranted and dangerous.', 1129, 0), (455763, 'The usefulness of religion - the fact that it gives life meaning, that it makes people feel good - is not an argument for the truth of any religious doctrine. It''s not an argument that it''s reasonable to believe that Jesus really was born of a virgin or that the Bible is the perfect word of the creator of the universe.', 1816, 0), (455764, 'India is a country in which every great religion finds a home.', 4208, 0), (455765, 'People have evolved into something selfish, greedy and intolerant. People are unaccepting, because of religion, race, gender, sexual orientation... I''ve seen it in punk clubs, and I''ve seen it in the world.', 358, 0), (455766, 'Religion doesn''t make people bigots. People are bigots and they use religion to justify their ideology.', 17517, 0), (455767, 'I don''t think that people accept the fact that life doesn''t make sense. I think it makes people terribly uncomfortable. It seems like religion and myth were invented against that, trying to make sense out of it.', 18666, 0), (455768, 'I was born poor and without religion, under a happy sky, feeling harmony, not hostility, in nature. I began not by feeling torn, but in plenitude.', 532, 0), (455769, 'I was never pushed into the religion by my mother or anyone else. I made up my own mind when I was old enough. I am not a religious person, but I am spiritual.', 47095, 0), (455770, 'Secularism is categorically not saying that the religious may not speak out publicly or have a say in public life. It is about saying that religion alone should not confer a privileged say in public life, or greater influence on it. It really is as simple as that.', 1716, 0), (455771, 'From a constitutional standpoint, the religion of a candidate is supposed to make no difference. Even before the founding fathers dreamed up the First Amendment, they inserted a provision in the Constitution expressly prohibiting any religious test for office.', 68675, 0), (455772, 'I sometimes wish I had been educated a Catholic, in order to unite the poetry of religion with its higher principles. Are they necessarily inseparable? Is man really so much of a philosopher, that he can conceive of truth in its abstract purity, and divest life and the affections of all the aids of the imagination?', 11482, 0), (455773, 'To repay evils with kindness is the religion I was taught to practise, and this will forever be my rule.', 13434, 0), (455774, 'We don''t understand why we''re here, no one''s giving us an answer, religion is vague, your parents can''t help because they''re just people, and it''s all terrible, and there''s no meaning to anything.', 69491, 0), (455775, 'I''ve never meditated in my life. I don''t practice yoga nor any religion. I''m a tourist on the realm of stillness.', 711, 0), (455776, 'At first, laws evolved out of religious doctrines. It followed that they were recognized only when advantageous to those who practiced the same religion and who appeared equals under the protection of the same gods. For the members of all other cults, there was neither law nor mercy.', 72772, 0), (455777, 'I was brought up Catholic and know the stench of the Catholic Church. I moved away from religion early, but the impression remains.', 5995, 0), (455778, 'The quarrels and divisions about religion were evils unknown to the heathen. The reason was because the religion of the heathen consisted rather in rites and ceremonies than in any constant belief.', 1035, 0), (455779, 'Other lands may have their charms, and the sunny skies of other climes may be regretted, but it is with pride and gladness that the wanderer sets foot again on British soil, thanking God for the religion and the liberty which have made this weather-beaten island in a northern sea to be the light and glory of the world.', 68866, 0), (455780, 'All religions and all communities have the same rights, and it is my responsibility to ensure their complete and total protection. My government will not tolerate or accept any discrimination based on caste, creed and religion.', 40212, 0), (455781, 'What we need is a system of thought - you might even call it a religion - that can bind humans together. A system that would fit the Republic of Chad as well as the United States: a system that would supply our idealistic young people with something to believe in.', 62519, 0), (455782, 'Equal protection under the law - for race, religion, gender or sexual orientation - should not be subject to the most popular sentiments of the day.', 10615, 0), (455783, 'Religious beliefs have played a vital role in forming America''s character as well as my own. I was raised as a Lutheran, and I believe in God and consider my faith and involvement with organized religion to be an important part of who I am.', 68241, 0), (455784, 'Is not the brand of ''double-dealer'' stamped on the forehead of every democratic slaveholder? Are not fraud and hypocrisy the religion of the man who calls himself a democrat, and hold his fellow-man in bondage?', 1859, 0), (455785, 'When I got religion, I found some work to do to benefit somebody.', 2013, 0), (455786, 'Religion is something we don''t talk about, and it is used by uneducated people as a weapon to divide us as opposed to connect with each other.', 68492, 0), (455787, 'Daredevil''s religion makes him unique. He''s a vigilante, but he''s also a lawyer - and all the while, he believes only God is capable of bringing people to justice.', 70730, 0), (455788, 'I was born and raised Catholic, so it''s in my blood. I don''t go to church... I was born and raised Catholic, which is about the extent of my religion. My parents made one request: that I have my first Holy Communion.', 71398, 0), (455789, 'Superstition is the only religion of which base souls are capable of.', 8895, 0), (455790, 'Religion is of general and public concern, and on its support depend, in great measure, the peace and good order of government, the safety and happiness of the people.', 72757, 0), (455791, 'People who dismiss science in favor of religion sometimes confuse the challenge of rigorously understanding the world with a deliberate intellectual exclusion that leads them to mistrust scientists and, to their detriment, what they discover.', 58935, 0), (455792, 'If you come out of the gate with a finger pointed, then you really aren''t opening the door to any sort of resolution to whatever the problem may be. Whether it''s about race or sexual orientation or religion, if you can''t empathize with the opposing party, then you can''t really meet in the middle.', 67336, 0), (455793, 'I am thankful I can see much to admire in all religions.', 43909, 0), (455794, 'Religion has caused more harm than any other idea since the beginning of time. There''s nothing good I can say about it. People use it as a crutch.', 69047, 0), (455795, 'Unfortunately, religion, like patriotism, is easy to misuse for political purposes.', 72773, 0), (455796, 'For that again, is what all manner of religion essentially is: childish dependency.', 22518, 0), (455797, 'The people who are teaching religion and not teaching love are missing the message.', 13964, 0), (455798, 'The First Amendment only says ''Congress shall make no law respecting an establishment of religion.'' It can disrespect all it wants.', 10731, 0), (455799, 'Terrorism should be seen in the light of the country''s security and not from the narrow perspective of caste, creed and religion.', 72774, 0), (455800, 'Some people think that religion is not essential to society. I do not hold this view. I consider the foundation of religion to be essential to the life and practices of a society.', 5224, 0);
